This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with speech translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Additionally, the paper proposes a new end-to-end trainable model with attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in NLP. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech recognition and translation, which are related to sound processing. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses the training and performance of different models. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with machine translation, which is a subfield of AI. 

Finally, cs.SD (Signal Processing) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with processing speech signals.
